-- Colombian Stock Movers: Grupo Aval, Canacol, Grupo Nutresa
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-18T16:55:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/colombian-stock-movers-grupo-aval-canacol-grupo-nutresa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:30 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.9 percent to 13,408.16, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.3 percent to 1,603.42.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA  (AVAL CB),  Colombia ’s
biggest banking group by assets, gained 1.1 percent to 1,200
pesos. The company said it is evaluating the possibility of an
overseas bond sale in meetings with investors, according to a
regulatory filing yesterday.  The company also created a Cayman Islands-based subsidiary,
Grupo Aval Ltd., without giving further details, the filing
said.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA)  (NUTRESA CB), Colombia’s biggest food
producer, rose 0.5 percent to 20,900 pesos.  Global coffee consumption will grow about 1.5 percent this
year as a slowdown in economic growth fails to deter consumers,
Roberio Silva, executive director of the  International Coffee
Organization , said today in an interview.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, rose 1.9 percent to
1,635 pesos. The company drilled the Cachalote-1st Well in
southern Colombia with results expected in two to three weeks,
according to a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
